{"id": "duc04-testb-24:8#24", "contents": "Three American researchers, Robert F. Furchgott, Louis J. Ignarro, and Ferid Murad, have been awarded the Nobel Medicine Prize for their groundbreaking discovery on how nitric oxide acts as a signal molecule in the cardiovascular system. This breakthrough has far-reaching applications, including the treatment of hardening of the arteries and impotence. The researchers, from the State University of New York, University of California-Los Angeles, and the University of Texas Medical School, respectively, have made significant contributions to the field of medicine."}
